        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 12:40PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1240 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brighton Park, or over South Lawndale, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Lawn, Chicago Lawn, Englewood, Oak Lawn, Oakland, West Elsdon,
Bridgeport, Near North Side, Stickney, Chicago Loop, Lower West Side,
McKinley Park, Avalon Park, Grand Boulevard, South Lawndale, Hyde
Park, South Shore, Near West Side, Woodlawn, Near South Side,
Evergreen Park, Armour Square, Fuller Park, Douglas, and Navy Pier.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
